headline: Rate-Cut Hopes Bolster These Stocks. Two Top Buy Points.
summary: Consumer stocks led the stock market Tuesday, as investors pounced on retail, travel and other splurge-on-me stocks.  Economic data was largely disappointing but appeared to raise hopes of another interest-rate cut.  In afternoon trading, eight of the 12 best-performing industry groups were from the retail sector — each up more than 4% and leading IBD's ranking of 197 groups.

headline: Planet Fitness Banks on Strategic Initiatives Amid High Attrition
summary: PLNT leans on franchise growth, marketing strength and digital upgrades even as attrition and rising costs challenge momentum.
